{# Methodology reference modal — static English content, included on all pages.
   Opened by the footer #methodology-link button, Esc/backdrop/close to dismiss.
   Accessibility mirrors the gate-modal (role=dialog, aria-modal, focus trap). #}
<div class="methodology-overlay" id="methodology-modal" hidden>
  <div class="methodology-modal" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="methodology-title">
    <button type="button" class="methodology-close" id="methodology-close" aria-label="Close">&times;</button>
    {% include "_rotation_illo.html.j2" %}
    <h2 id="methodology-title">How the scanner works</h2>
    <div class="methodology-body">
      <p>Sector Momentum ranks US and European stock-market sectors — and a set of
         thematic ETFs — by price-momentum strength, refreshed daily. It is
         analytical tooling, not investment advice.</p>

      <h3>Universe</h3>
      <p>The US cohort is the 11 SPDR Select Sector ETFs (GICS sectors). The European
         cohort is 14 STOXX Europe 600 sector ETFs, including the standalone Banks,
         Financial Services and Insurance funds and the Basic Resources and Chemicals
         funds (split from their old GICS composites in July 2026). Benchmarks are RSP
         (equal-weight S&amp;P 500) for the US and EXSA.DE (STOXX Europe 600) for Europe.
         A separate thematic-ETF cohort is scored against ACWI.</p>

      <h3>Data sources</h3>
      <p>Daily OHLCV prices come from stooq, falling back to yfinance, cached locally
         with weekend/holiday-aware freshness so the latest close is pulled each
         trading day. News sentiment is computed from GDELT DOC 2.0 English headlines
         scored with the ProsusAI/FinBERT model. Macro context shows SPY versus its
         200-day moving average and the VIX volatility band.</p>

      <h3>Signals</h3>
      <p>Each sector is measured on two pillars:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Level</strong> — where the sector stands now: <code>rs_ratio</code>
            (RRG relative strength vs the benchmark), 3-month return, 6-month return,
            and whether price is above its 50-day moving average.</li>
        <li><strong>Change</strong> — how that is evolving: <code>rs_momentum</code>
            (RRG relative-strength momentum, 5-day lookback), acceleration, 50-DMA
            slope, and on-balance-volume (OBV) slope.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Constituent breadth — the share of a US sector's S&amp;P 500 members trading
         above their own 50-DMA — is shown for context only (European sectors show
         &ldquo;&mdash;&rdquo;). FinBERT news sentiment is shown per sector. The 200-day
         moving-average level was dropped from scoring in July 2026 after a correlation
         audit found it highly collinear with the 50-DMA; it remains visible for
         reference.</p>

      <h3>Scoring</h3>
      <p>Every signal is standardized (z-scored) <em>across sectors within its own
         region</em> — US sectors are ranked against US sectors, European against
         European. The signals form two equal-weighted pillars, and the composite is
         <strong>50% Level + 50% Change</strong>. Sectors are then ranked within each
         region by composite. Sentiment is <strong>informational only</strong> and does
         not move the ranking; the leaderboard offers an optional toggle to blend it in
         client-side at a weight you choose, but the canonical ranking is pure price
         data.</p>

      <h3>Trajectory &amp; setup badges</h3>
      <p>A sector's trajectory is the slope of its rank over the last five scans
         (&uarr;&uarr; / &uarr; / &rarr; / &darr; / &darr;&darr;). An <strong>Entry</strong>
         badge appears when a sector has a positive composite, a positive Change score,
         and a rising trajectory; an <strong>Exit</strong> badge appears when it is
         falling with a negative Change score.</p>

      <h3>Backtest</h3>
      <p>The Backtest tab replays a simple monthly rotation into the top-N sectors
         versus the region benchmark, point-in-time (no look-ahead), using the price
         pillars only, with optional transaction costs.</p>

      <h3>Research basis</h3>
      <p>Design changes are validated before adoption. The European composites were
         split into their true STOXX sub-sectors after the blends were found to average
         away real momentum differences; the 200-DMA signal was dropped after the
         correlation audit; and FinBERT news polarity replaced Google Trends as the
         sentiment source in July 2026.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<script>
(function () {
  var modal = document.getElementById("methodology-modal");
  if (!modal || modal.dataset.bound) { return; }
  modal.dataset.bound = "1";
  var panel = modal.querySelector('[role="dialog"]');
  var closeBtn = document.getElementById("methodology-close");
  var lastFocus = null;

  function focusables() {
    return panel.querySelectorAll(
      'button, a[href], input, [tabindex]:not([tabindex="-1"])');
  }
  function open() {
    lastFocus = document.activeElement;
    modal.hidden = false;
    (closeBtn || panel).focus();
    document.addEventListener("keydown", onKey);
  }
  function close() {
    modal.hidden = true;
    document.removeEventListener("keydown", onKey);
    if (lastFocus && lastFocus.focus) { lastFocus.focus(); }
  }
  function onKey(e) {
    if (e.key === "Escape") { close(); return; }
    if (e.key === "Tab") {
      var f = focusables();
      if (!f.length) { return; }
      var first = f[0], last = f[f.length - 1];
      if (e.shiftKey && document.activeElement === first) { e.preventDefault(); last.focus(); }
      else if (!e.shiftKey && document.activeElement === last) { e.preventDefault(); first.focus(); }
    }
  }
  modal.addEventListener("click", function (e) { if (e.target === modal) { close(); } });
  if (closeBtn) { closeBtn.addEventListener("click", close); }

  function bindTrigger() {
    var link = document.getElementById("methodology-link");
    if (link) { link.addEventListener("click", function (e) { e.preventDefault(); open(); }); }
    if (location.hash === "#methodology") { open(); }
  }
  if (document.readyState === "loading") {
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", bindTrigger);
  } else {
    bindTrigger();
  }
})();
</script>
